The paper proposes a new scoring function for structure learning of Bayesian networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the complexity penalty and conditional independence tests, which are concepts related to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper presents empirical results and discusses search algorithms, which are topics related to computational intelligence and optimization (cs.SI).
